text:
General View

303-5 East 36th Street, (St. Gabriel's branch New York Public Library), adjoining the N. E. corner of Second Avenue, showing a general view from atop this structure which is shortly to be demolished. Two views are westward and show the Empire State Building at Fifth Avenue and 34th Street. The larger of the others is northward in direction, to show the graceful Chrysler Building on Lexington Avenue at 42nd Street. The last photo is towards Fifth Avenue and 42nd Street, showing mainly the No. 10 E. 40th Street Building.

Fall 1939
Views 1, 2, 3, and 4

Gift of Beecher Ogden
title: General view - [Manhattan - 36th Street (East) - St. Gabriel's branch of the New York Public Library.]

text:
General View.

303-5 E. 36th Street, (St. Gabriel's branch New york Public Library) adjoining the N. E. corner of Second Avenue, showing a general view of the excavation that will include the present vantage point. This photo is northeastward towards First Avenue and E. 37th Street to show buildings upon same and the Midtown Queens Tunnel emerging there.

September 1939

Gift of Beecher Ogden
